## § 3.0 Design System and Layout

### § 3.1 Color Palette

**Applicable to all pages of the website unless given clear direction to use a different color**

- **Main Background:** `#222831`
- **Section/Div Backgrounds:** `#31363F`
- **Primary Text:**` #76ABAE`
- **Secondary Text/Subheadings:**`#EEEEEE`
- **Button Background:**  `#31363F`
- **Button Text:**  `#EEEEEE`
- **Button Hover:**`#415780`

### § 3.2 Navigation Bar

- Rather than a traditional navigation bar, there will be three buttons on the right hand side laid out horizontally with even spacing that is appealing to the eye:
  - One button should say "login" and lead to a login page (other features of this page will be added later)
  - One button should say "create" and leads to a create page (other features of this page will be added later)
  - One button should say "lexicon" that will lead to a page that lists all the words they have added or created (other features of this page will be added later)
- On the top left corner should be the word FLIP and when clicked should lead back to the home page
- Navigation bar should be featured on every page of the website

### § 3.3 Homepage

- Centered on the page should be the flashcard

### § 3.4 Flashcard Component

- The flashcard should be in this color `#435446` with the text in this color `#9ab0a2`
- The flashcard should have a smooth flipping motion
- The front of the card should use the target language (for now use Korean and as a placeholder use the Korean word for hello = 안녕하세요)
- The back of the card should use the user's native language (for now use English and as a placeholder use the word "hello" as the translation)
- Beneath the flashcard, but not part of the flashcard should be three buttons:
  - One button that toggles the flip (button should be named "flip")
  - One button that moves onto the next card (button should be named "next")
  - One button that shuffles the set (button should be named "shuffle")

### § 3.5 Create Page

- On this page there should be two columns where the user can input information:
  - One column to input vocabulary for the target language
  - One column to input the translation in the native language
- Only have one row as a placeholder for now
- Underneath the two columns should be two buttons:
  - One button should say "import"
  - One button should say "submit"
- On the right hand side should be a space with a subheading that says "tags" (further instruction will be given on this section. As a placeholder use the text "#text")

